<!-- SELLING IN FLORIDA (accurate: certificate of destruction + derelict cert) -->
<section class="sec fl">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head center"><span class="eyebrow">Selling a Car in Florida</span><h2>With a title — or without one</h2><p>Most buyers won't explain this part. Here's how it actually works when you sell a junk or end-of-life vehicle to a licensed yard like ours.</p></div>
    <div class="fl-grid">
      <div class="fl-card">
        <span class="flag">📋 If you have the title</span>
        <h3>Sign it over — we do the rest</h3>
        <ul class="fl-list">
          <li><span class="ck">✓</span><span>You sign the title over to us. Because the vehicle is headed for dismantling, it's processed for a <b>Certificate of Destruction</b> (Form HSMV 82363).</span></li>
          <li><span class="ck">✓</span><span>Your title record is then marked <b>"Cancelled (Junked)"</b> — so the vehicle can't come back on you and can never be re-titled.</span></li>
          <li><span class="ck">✓</span><span><b>Keep your license plate.</b> In Florida the plate stays with you, the seller.</span></li>
          <li><span class="ck">✓</span><span>As a <b>licensed Florida salvage dealer</b>, we handle the form and the filing for you.</span></li>
        </ul>
        <div class="src">Source: FLHSMV <a href="https://www.flhsmv.gov/pdf/forms/82363.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Form 82363</a>; Fla. Stat. <a href="https://www.flsenate.gov/laws/statutes/2023/319.30" target="_blank" rel="noopener">§ 319.30</a>.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="fl-card">
        <span class="flag">🔑 No title? You still have options</span>
        <h3>Florida's derelict-vehicle pathway</h3>
        <ul class="fl-list">
          <li><span class="ck">✓</span><span>When a title isn't available, Florida lets a <b>licensed salvage dealer</b> (that's us) take the vehicle on a <b>Derelict Motor Vehicle Certificate</b>.</span></li>
          <li><span class="ck">✓</span><span>It applies to vehicles <b>worth under $1,000</b> and <b>at least 10 model years old</b>. The form can be signed by the owner or whoever lawfully has the vehicle.</span></li>
          <li><span class="ck">✓</span><span>There's a short holding period (about <b>3 business days</b>) before it's dismantled, and it can never be titled again.</span></li>
          <li><span class="ck">✓</span><span>It's the legal way to handle a no-title junk car — done by the book.</span></li>
        </ul>
        <div class="src">Source: FLHSMV <a href="https://www.flhsmv.gov/motor-vehicles-tags-titles/junk-vehicle-tag-title/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Junk a Vehicle</a>; <a href="https://www.flhsmv.gov/pdf/forms/82137.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Form 82137</a>.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="callout" style="max-width:760px;margin:22px auto 0;text-align:center">Not sure what you've got? <a href="tel:{{ siteSettings.phoneNumber|replace({"-": ""}) }}"><b>Call {{ siteSettings.phoneNumber }}</b></a> and we'll tell you exactly what applies to your vehicle.</div>
  </div>
</section>

