<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="sec">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head center"><span class="eyebrow">Questions, Answered</span><h2>Selling your car in Florida: FAQ</h2></div>
    <div class="faq">
      <details open><summary>How do I sell my car to Kiker's? <span class="pm">+</span></summary><div class="ans">Call <b>{{ siteSettings.phoneNumber }}</b> or fill out the form with your vehicle's year, make, model, and condition. We give you a fair cash offer fast, schedule a same-day or convenient pickup, tow it free, handle the paperwork, and pay you on the spot.</div></details>
      <details><summary>Do you buy cars that don't run? <span class="pm">+</span></summary><div class="ans">Yes. We buy <b>running and non-running vehicles</b> — wrecked, flooded, blown engine or transmission, or just worn out. It doesn't have to start, and it doesn't have to be pretty.</div></details>
      <details><summary>Can I sell my car without a title in Florida? <span class="pm">+</span></summary><div class="ans">Often, yes. When a title isn't available, Florida lets a <b>licensed salvage dealer</b> like Kiker's take the vehicle on a <b>Derelict Motor Vehicle Certificate</b> — generally for vehicles worth under $1,000 and at least 10 model years old. Call us and we'll tell you what applies.</div></details>
      <details><summary>Do I keep my license plate when I sell? <span class="pm">+</span></summary><div class="ans">Yes. In Florida the <b>license plate stays with you, the seller</b>, not the vehicle. Pull it before the car leaves.</div></details>
      <details><summary>Will the car still be in my name after I sell it? <span class="pm">+</span></summary><div class="ans">No. For a junked vehicle, the title is processed for a <b>Certificate of Destruction</b> and marked "Cancelled (Junked)," so it's permanently off your name and can't be re-titled. We handle that filing as a licensed Florida salvage dealer.</div></details>
      <details><summary>How much is my car worth? <span class="pm">+</span></summary><div class="ans">It depends on the year, make and model, whether it runs, what parts are still on it, the condition, and <b>current scrap and metal prices</b>. We give you a fair, no-haggle offer for your specific vehicle.</div></details>
      <details><summary>Do scrap prices really affect my offer? <span class="pm">+</span></summary><div class="ans">Yes. Metals like <b>copper, steel, and aluminum</b> set the floor on a junk vehicle's value, and those prices move daily. When copper is strong, wiring and components are worth more.</div></details>
      <details><summary>How fast can you pick up my vehicle? <span class="pm">+</span></summary><div class="ans">Often the <b>same day</b>. Or pick a time that works for you — you're in control of the schedule. Towing is <b>free</b> across the Pensacola area.</div></details>
      <details><summary>What areas do you serve? <span class="pm">+</span></summary><div class="ans">We buy vehicles in <b>Pensacola, Pace, Milton and East Milton, Cantonment</b>, and nearby — across Escambia and Santa Rosa counties.</div></details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

